  "excerpt": "Time to swap the duvet for something a little less sweltering. We're reaching for picks from Brooklinen, Boll \u0026 Branch and a few more vetted lightweight options.",
  "siteName": "Architectural Digest",
  "favicon": "",
  "text": "More Blankets We're BrowsingBrooklinen Featherweight Bed BlanketAnother AD bedding favorite, Brooklinen’s down alternative blanket strikes the perfect balance between a bulky duvet and throw blanket. It looks as plush as any down duvet, but it remains featherweight in feel, perfect for hot sleepers who are looking for a cozy choice that won’t make them overheat. The 525 fill power is wrapped in a 100% cotton sateen shell, so the fabric feels light and silky on your skin. No duvet cover needed here, but if you’re tempted, Brooklinen has some great options for those too (all Oeko-Tex certified).Bearaby Knit Weighted BlanketA vetted celebrity and designer favorite, this chunky knit has appeared in many a home tour at AD. Its thick knit weave makes for a cozy throw, the perfect couch accessory, or finishing touch folded up at the bottom of the bed. It’s also one of our favorite weighted blankets, in case you find you can’t help but need a bit of weight to achieve REM.The Loomia Sophie Throw BlanketThis Turkish throw certainly delivers as a piece of home decor. The bohemian weave, minimal stripe, and cream color bring an earthy and worldly vibe to a room, making it an especially good pairing for a couch that feels perhaps too new or too modern for a space, and needs a little grounding. The king size is perfect for swaddling, and 100% cotton keeps it lofty.BOURINA Jacquard Argyle Throw BlanketWith 44 color options, there’s plenty to choose from to match your home’s aesthetic. This textured throw blanket is made from 100% acrylic fabric, which ensures a plush texture and airy feel, making it a perfect throw for both warm and cold weather—keeping you comfy without getting too toasty. The texture plays on cable knit without going full preppy, and the zigzag lends the fabric a nice drape.DII Chevron Collection Throw BlanketThis herringbone style works double duty as an all-season blanket as well as a home decor element. The pattern can add a necessary texture or color to a solid-color couch, and it lends a coziness to a living room that might lean too industrial or minimalist. The 20 different hues (though keep a close watch, they often come in and out of stock) allow you to play with the color story you’re after, but for our part, we think a pop of red is always a good idea. Plus, both blue and green can bring a serene design element to a space.How We ChoseWhen pulling from Amazon, we first focused onour bedding brand go-tos, including Boll \u0026 Branch, Buffy, and Brooklinen. These retailers nearly always rank well for us because of their products’ high-quality materials, reasonable price points, and hand-feel. We wanted to make sure these were as breathable and lightweight as they claimed, so our editors and contributors shared several they think are suitable for sweltering nights. From there, we sought out other highly-rated blankets on Amazon and cross-checked their material makeup and ratings to see just why reviewers loved them.",
