t_card\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;total_index\u0026#34;:1,\u0026#34;hasMultipleImage\u0026#34;:false,\u0026#34;componentType\u0026#34;:true,\u0026#34;showProsConsData\u0026#34;:false,\u0026#34;videoIds\u0026#34;:[]}\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch3 id=\"upc_685c240e3b24f962484c285c\" type=\"embed\"\u003eDII Chevron Collection Throw Blanket\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis herringbone style works double duty as an all-season blanket as well as a home decor element. The pattern can add a necessary texture or color to a solid-color couch, and it lends a coziness to a living room that might lean too industrial or minimalist. The 20 different hues (though keep a close watch, they often come in and out of stock) allow you to play with the color story you’re after, but for our part, we think a pop of red is always a good idea. Plus, both blue and green can bring a serene design element to a space.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp id=\"how-we-chose\" tabindex=\"-1\"\u003e\u003ch2\u003eHow We Chose\u003c/h2\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhen pulling from Amazon, we first focused onour bedding brand go-tos, including Boll \u0026amp; Branch, Buffy, and Brooklinen. These retailers nearly always rank well for us because of their products’ high-quality materials, reasonable price points, and hand-feel. We wanted to make sure these were as breathable and lightweight as they claimed, so our editors and contributors shared several they think are suitable for sweltering nights. From there, we sought out other highly-rated blankets on Amazon and cross-checked their material makeup and ratings to see just why reviewers loved them.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
